CODING & COLLABORATION PLATFORMS

----------------------------------------

Introduction

In this task, I explored different digital platforms used for coding and collaboration. These platforms help students improve their skills, practice coding, and work together efficiently.

----------------------------------------

Coding Platform (HackerRank)

HackerRank is an online platform used for practicing coding and improving problem-solving skills. I created an account and solved a beginner-level problem.

Through this activity, I learned:
• Basic coding concepts  
• Logical thinking and problem-solving  
• Importance of practice in programming  

This platform is useful for preparing for coding interviews and improving technical skills.

----------------------------------------

Google Forms

Google Forms is a tool used to create surveys, quizzes, and collect data. I created a form titled “Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz.”

The form includes:
• Multiple-choice questions  
• Short answer questions  

The purpose of the form is to check awareness about digital literacy among students.

